  "texts": [
    "IntroductionThe industrial sector underwent a few revolutions.",
    "Industry 4.0 (I4.0) [1][2][3], often referred to as the Fourth Industrial Revolution (4IR), indicates tremendous technological progress for the industrial sector in this century.",
    "The revolution that officially started over a decade ago aims to integrate current state-of-the-art technologies like artificial intelligence (AI) and its applications [4] in production processes to especially for less-skilled workers.",
    "AI branches and their applications are still the driving forces behind the technological implementation of I5.0.",
    "They contribute to developing resilient, sustainable, and human-centric [10] manufacturing tools, processes, and systems that help human operators upskill their expertise and preserve the environment from overconsumption and wastage [11].One way through which I5.0 aims to reinsert human beings at the center of factory operations and production systems is by improving the human-to-machine interaction process by integrating personalized and contextualized natural language to ease collaboration from the human perspective."
  ],
